1 WHEREAS, the SAVE America Act would establish uniform voter identification
2 requirements for federal elections, ensuring that every vote is cast by an eligible voter and
3 that election procedures are transparent and secure; and
4 WHEREAS, ensuring election integrity is not a partisan issue but a fundamental
5 responsibility owed to every American citizen.
6 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
7 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby memorialize the United States Congress to take such
8 actions as are necessary to pass the SAVE America Act requiring voter identification for
9 federal elections.
10 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the Legislature
11 of Louisiana hereby expresses its strong support for policies that safeguard election integrity,
12 prevent fraud, and strengthen public confidence in the democratic process.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
14 presiding officers of the Senate and the House of Representatives of the Congress of the
15 United States of America and to each member of the Louisiana congressional delegation.
